Instead of using ```move_uploaded_file()```, call a function called, say, ```compressFile()```:

```
compressFile($_FILES[&quot;file&quot;][&quot;tmp_name&quot;], $targetFilePath, $quality) //Quality can be anything you want between 0-100
```
where ```compressImage()``` can be something like (assuming you want to, for example, compress JPEG, GIFs, etc.)

```
    function compressFile($source, $destination, $quality){
		$info = getimagesize($source);

		if ($info[&#39;mime&#39;] == &#39;image/jpeg&#39;) 
			$image = imagecreatefromjpeg($source);

		elseif ($info[&#39;mime&#39;] == &#39;image/gif&#39;) 
			$image = imagecreatefromgif($source);

		elseif ($info[&#39;mime&#39;] == &#39;image/png&#39;) 
			$image = imagecreatefrompng($source);

		if(imagejpeg($image, $destination, $quality)){
          return true;
        } else {
          return false;
        }
    }
```
